  Its easy to get to if you have 3 things - sow, invis (for the first part), and an enchanter to control aggro.  Go up to the Front Gate of Mistmoore, and cross over the bridge.  Once inside, follow the hall to the right -- all the way to the piano room.  Outside is the courtyard, you have to go out there, turn right and go to the corner of the courtyard where the fountain is.  In the far corner of the area with the fountain, you will find the bone (ribcage?) that you need.<br>
<br>
 Now, as far as the mobs.  You can invis and go right up to the front gate, but once you get inside, near the piano room there are undead that will aggro and make you vis, then get more live aggro, so chanter is good to have.  If you and the pally are there, you will be able to hack anything that comes at you as long as you dont get more than 2 at a time.<br>
<br>
  When I did it, I was all alone.  Just grabbed a sow potion, an invis potion and had my finger twiching my Lay on Hands.  Drank the SOW, drank the invis, ran up and got undead aggro near the piano room.  With them smackin' me I ran to the fountain area, searched and found the bone (I had no idea where it was at), had to use LOH but managed to grab it and run.  Ran out the front door, shouted TRAIN TO ZONE and made it out. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
  I completed Holy Might spell quest with no outside help except for the last guy, where I paid 100pp to 5 higher level people to ensure we were able to take the guy out.<br>
<br>
  If you want to hear a real harrowing experience, let me tell you how I got the finger bone from Phinny's lair, having never been there, naked and alone... without dying!<br>
<br>
They say paladins are useless, but when it comes to questing, none do it better.<br>
<br>
